main event: A white light was observed crossing the northeast sky in Rolla, Missouri on October 6, 1965.
interesting points: The light was steady and did not blink, traveling in a southeasterly direction.
The report concluded the object was likely a satellite, but acknowledged the visual characteristics did not match known satellites or space probes.
The National Investigations Committee on Aerial Phenomena (NICAP) expressed concern over the continued secrecy and deception surrounding UFOs by the U.S. Air Force's Project Blue Book.
NICAP claimed overwhelming evidence, much of it classified, points to UFOs being real and of extraterrestrial origin, posing a threat to national security.
The report included an additional letter from a person describing unexplained objects that were too large to be planes, did not make noise or emit exhaust, and appeared to hover or maneuver.
sighted object: A white light crossing the northeast sky
